1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,544
(A few days ago)

3
00:01:37,544 --> 00:01:40,065
Lately, the company's
really cracking down

4
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:43,184
on employees reselling gift wines
and discounted liquor.

5
00:01:44,625 --> 00:01:46,145
We've stationed some people

6
00:01:46,345 --> 00:01:48,225
at various tobacco and liquor
retail points.

7
00:01:49,104 --> 00:01:51,304
Then someone showed up,

8
00:01:51,304 --> 00:01:53,425
trying to sell
a case of 25-year-old Gennadiy.

9
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:54,664
Our guys questioned him.

10
00:01:55,384 --> 00:01:56,865
But he just turned and ran.

11
00:01:57,425 --> 00:01:58,705
(Ou Yang)
They panicked

12
00:01:58,904 --> 00:01:59,824
(Internal Auditor, GST Liquor China)
and called the police.

13
00:02:00,384 --> 00:02:01,664
We had no idea

14
00:02:02,145 --> 00:02:03,585
that he was your husband.

15
00:02:21,185 --> 00:02:22,065
Here, Officer.

16
00:02:22,345 --> 00:02:24,465
Honey, I didn't mean to
cause you trouble.

17
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:27,065
I didn't expect
that someone was stationed there.

18
00:02:28,225 --> 00:02:29,144
You didn't expect it?

19
00:02:30,264 --> 00:02:31,704
You didn't expect anything.

20
00:02:31,704 --> 00:02:33,144
You didn't expect to get laid off.

21
00:02:33,785 --> 00:02:35,945
You didn't expect your stocks
to plummet.

22
00:02:36,264 --> 00:02:37,984
You didn't expect that the "investment"

23
00:02:37,984 --> 00:02:38,664
was a scam.

24
00:02:38,785 --> 00:02:40,025
You didn't expect to be caught

25
00:02:40,025 --> 00:02:40,945
reselling the liquors.

26
00:02:42,144 --> 00:02:42,664
Yao Xiaohui.

27
00:02:43,704 --> 00:02:44,264
I have

28
00:02:44,264 --> 00:02:45,584
only suffered in this marriage.

29
00:02:46,264 --> 00:02:48,144
I'm paying your one-million debt.

30
00:02:48,144 --> 00:02:49,465
And I'm raising your daughter.

31
00:02:49,704 --> 00:02:51,345
Have I ever complained to you?

32
00:02:52,025 --> 00:02:52,945
I told myself

33
00:02:53,225 --> 00:02:54,864
that it wasn't your fault.

34
00:02:55,025 --> 00:02:55,584
Right?

35
00:02:56,424 --> 00:02:57,625
But could you please

36
00:02:57,625 --> 00:02:58,864
not ruin my job

37
00:02:58,864 --> 00:03:00,424
when I'm paying your debt?

38
00:03:00,704 --> 00:03:01,945
Having a job these days

39
00:03:01,945 --> 00:03:03,424
isn't easy for me.

40
00:03:05,345 --> 00:03:06,225
I'm sorry, honey.

41
00:03:06,785 --> 00:03:07,824
Don't touch me.

42
00:03:14,025 --> 00:03:16,345
(This is the apartment
I have to sell to pay off debts.)

43
00:03:16,625 --> 00:03:18,945
(Nine years in sales, killing myself.)

44
00:03:18,945 --> 00:03:20,144
(Back to square one.)

45
00:03:21,305 --> 00:03:22,984
(No, I can't fall apart.)

46
00:03:23,945 --> 00:03:25,745
(Yao Xiaohui, I'll pay your debts.)

47
00:03:25,945 --> 00:03:27,305
(But you must divorce me first.)

48
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:37,416
(Nobody Earns Money Standing Tall)

49
00:03:40,872 --> 00:03:44,328
=Episode 8=
(Nepotism Hire)

50
00:03:44,735 --> 00:03:49,215
(Hotel Inn, Fuqiang Hotel
Accommodation: 2nd Floor)

51
00:04:10,264 --> 00:04:11,065
Repayment plan.

52
00:04:13,345 --> 00:04:14,225
Divorce agreement.

53
00:04:22,704 --> 00:04:24,344
He owes you 2.03 million total.

54
00:04:25,305 --> 00:04:26,344
After we divorce,

55
00:04:26,344 --> 00:04:27,704
we'll sell our apartment

56
00:04:27,704 --> 00:04:28,985
for about 1.2 million.

57
00:04:29,745 --> 00:04:30,904
My 600,000 share goes to you.

58
00:04:30,904 --> 00:04:32,024
I won't take a single cent.

59
00:04:32,904 --> 00:04:34,344
For the remaining 830,000,

60
00:04:34,584 --> 00:04:35,665
I'll pay 300,000 for him,

61
00:04:36,305 --> 00:04:37,625
10,000 yuan per month.

62
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:38,625
Paid off in 30 months.

63
00:04:39,144 --> 00:04:40,065
Thirty months?

64
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:43,024
That's way too slow.

65
00:04:47,464 --> 00:04:49,185
I can show you my payslip.

66
00:04:50,625 --> 00:04:53,344
With a child to raise, 10,000 a month

67
00:04:53,344 --> 00:04:54,224
is a challenge.

68
00:04:54,224 --> 00:04:55,505
I can't do any better.

69
00:04:56,185 --> 00:04:58,464
Actually, he borrowed from you
for personal use

70
00:04:58,464 --> 00:04:59,745
without my consent.

71
00:05:00,305 --> 00:05:01,824
I've consulted a lawyer.

72
00:05:02,784 --> 00:05:05,505
This counts as his personal debt.

73
00:05:06,144 --> 00:05:07,625
I have zero obligation to repay it.

74
00:05:08,425 --> 00:05:09,545
If negotiations turn sour,

75
00:05:09,545 --> 00:05:10,865
we'll just fall out.

76
00:05:11,665 --> 00:05:12,745
What a surprise.

77
00:05:13,105 --> 00:05:16,305
You loser married such a good wife.

78
00:05:17,344 --> 00:05:19,784
She's so far out of your league.

79
00:05:20,904 --> 00:05:22,665
Why not cover a larger portion for him?

80
00:05:23,505 --> 00:05:24,425
How about half?

81
00:05:31,305 --> 00:05:32,065
360,000.

82
00:05:33,584 --> 00:05:34,505
In three years.

83
00:05:34,505 --> 00:05:35,625
That's my final offer.

84
00:05:39,865 --> 00:05:40,344
Okay.

85
00:05:42,745 --> 00:05:43,784
Sir, it's ready.

86
00:05:49,185 --> 00:05:49,985
Looks good.

87
00:05:50,745 --> 00:05:51,665
Alright.

88
00:05:52,464 --> 00:05:53,065
Wait.

89
00:05:54,425 --> 00:05:55,144
He signs first.

90
00:05:56,505 --> 00:05:57,185
Yeah.

91
00:05:58,545 --> 00:06:01,425
You must get divorced first
for this to take effect.

92
00:06:02,665 --> 00:06:03,545
Sign the paper.

93
00:06:03,865 --> 00:06:05,985
Otherwise, pay now.

94
00:06:06,425 --> 00:06:08,144
If there's no objection, just sign it.

95
00:06:09,224 --> 00:06:10,185
Hurry up.

96
00:06:10,384 --> 00:06:12,545
She is such an amazing woman.

97
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,824
Don't ruin her future.

98
00:06:21,745 --> 00:06:24,904
I-I want to visit Weiwei.

99
00:06:29,344 --> 00:06:30,105
No problem.

100
00:06:30,904 --> 00:06:34,144
The contract says twice a month.
Is that okay?

101
00:06:50,224 --> 00:06:53,704
I-I need the restroom.

102
00:06:55,904 --> 00:06:57,545
Losers always have excuses.

103
00:07:17,745 --> 00:07:18,545
Are you done?

104
00:07:21,185 --> 00:07:21,704
You there?

105
00:07:26,105 --> 00:07:27,425
Sir, he's gone.

106
00:07:38,224 --> 00:07:40,344
How dare he pull this trick on me?

107
00:07:59,224 --> 00:08:00,305
Enjoy your meal.

108
00:08:00,505 --> 00:08:00,985
Thank you.

109
00:08:01,584 --> 00:08:02,264
Mr. Lai, come on.

110
00:08:02,264 --> 00:08:03,224
Dig in.

111
00:08:03,305 --> 00:08:03,904
Okay, thanks.

112
00:08:04,505 --> 00:08:05,224
Go ahead.

113
00:08:05,224 --> 00:08:06,865
I wish I had these skills.

114
00:08:06,865 --> 00:08:09,665
Then I could
slowly skin Yao Xiaohui alive.

115
00:08:12,425 --> 00:08:13,425
She was just kidding.

116
00:08:13,745 --> 00:08:15,985
Mr. Lai, should we get some drinks?

117
00:08:16,425 --> 00:08:16,865
Sure.

118
00:08:16,865 --> 00:08:18,625
No, I don't drink during work hours.

119
00:08:20,105 --> 00:08:20,865
Well then,

120
00:08:20,865 --> 00:08:23,024
I'll buy you drinks
when you're off work.

121
00:08:23,185 --> 00:08:25,545
I'll get Mr. Lai
some of our company's liquor.

122
00:08:25,545 --> 00:08:26,305
Good idea.

123
00:08:26,305 --> 00:08:27,904
Thanks, you're too kind.

124
00:08:27,904 --> 00:08:29,665
Then we'll toast with tea instead.

125
00:08:29,665 --> 00:08:30,464
Okay.

126
00:08:32,864 --> 00:08:33,425
Ms. Liang.

127
00:08:34,864 --> 00:08:36,704
If your husband refuses to divorce you,

128
00:08:37,224 --> 00:08:39,104
you'll have to wait another six months.

129
00:08:40,104 --> 00:08:43,065
Gather evidence for loss of affection
and file for divorce.

130
00:08:43,545 --> 00:08:45,665
Take the kid
and lie low in your parents'.

131
00:08:46,425 --> 00:08:48,744
To be honest, Mr. Lai,

132
00:08:48,744 --> 00:08:50,785
my kid and I
are already staying at my parents'.

133
00:08:51,104 --> 00:08:53,224
He lives alone
in the apartment we bought.

134
00:08:53,984 --> 00:08:54,584
The apartment?

135
00:08:55,305 --> 00:08:55,864
You bought it

136
00:08:56,504 --> 00:08:57,344
after marriage?

137
00:08:57,665 --> 00:08:58,545
Yeah.

138
00:08:59,104 --> 00:09:00,984
But he paid the bulk of it

139
00:09:01,104 --> 00:09:02,584
and covered the mortgage before.

140
00:09:03,744 --> 00:09:05,744
Her husband used to be a decent guy.

141
00:09:05,945 --> 00:09:07,305
But then he got laid off.

142
00:09:07,545 --> 00:09:09,185
He fell for those "investment" scams

143
00:09:09,624 --> 00:09:10,905
and got hooked on gambling.

144
00:09:11,984 --> 00:09:12,864
Indeed.

145
00:09:12,864 --> 00:09:16,545
Adversity tests a person severely.

146
00:09:18,545 --> 00:09:19,945
Does he have any other assets?

147
00:09:21,665 --> 00:09:22,464
No.

148
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:24,104
All he's got is his life.

149
00:09:24,785 --> 00:09:26,785
Is it worth anything? Probably not.

150
00:09:28,744 --> 00:09:29,665
Then just wait.

151
00:09:30,545 --> 00:09:31,864
He has a gambling addiction,

152
00:09:31,864 --> 00:09:32,704
refusing to change.

153
00:09:32,968 --> 00:09:34,408
The court will grant the divorce.

154
00:09:34,665 --> 00:09:36,704
No, Mr. Lai, I really can't wait.

155
00:09:37,305 --> 00:09:37,905
I'm not sure

156
00:09:37,905 --> 00:09:38,905
how things will go

157
00:09:39,025 --> 00:09:41,744
but his gambling debts
will certainly pile up.

158
00:09:44,224 --> 00:09:45,864
I see. Alright.

159
00:09:46,385 --> 00:09:47,464
I'll try my best.

160
00:09:48,185 --> 00:09:49,385
Don't just try. Make it work.

161
00:09:49,905 --> 00:09:50,464
To you.

162
00:09:50,905 --> 00:09:51,824
Please come again.

163
00:09:51,824 --> 00:09:52,665
Thank you.

164
00:09:59,305 --> 00:10:00,425
Here's 500,000.

165
00:10:00,425 --> 00:10:01,305
You know the PIN.

166
00:10:02,425 --> 00:10:03,025
Knock it off.

167
00:10:05,665 --> 00:10:07,665
Yao Xiaohui simply wants money.

168
00:10:07,665 --> 00:10:08,864
This is to buy your divorce.

169
00:10:08,864 --> 00:10:09,945
Settle this with him.

170
00:10:10,385 --> 00:10:11,025
No, no.

171
00:10:11,864 --> 00:10:13,665
You'll pay it back. It's not a gift.

172
00:10:13,744 --> 00:10:14,744
Don't overthink it.

173
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:16,704
I'm not overthinking, sis.

174
00:10:17,025 --> 00:10:19,145
I can't let him think I still have cash.

175
00:10:19,584 --> 00:10:20,744
I need him to believe

176
00:10:20,744 --> 00:10:22,464
that I'm completely broke.

177
00:10:22,464 --> 00:10:24,344
Then he might show mercy and let me go.

178
00:10:24,344 --> 00:10:25,385
Did it work?

179
00:10:32,385 --> 00:10:33,785
I just don't get it.

180
00:10:34,385 --> 00:10:36,224
How did he turn out like this?

181
00:10:36,385 --> 00:10:38,984
He scored 149 in math
on the college entrance exam.

182
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:40,704
Such a high score.

183
00:10:40,824 --> 00:10:42,145
Others are building rockets.

184
00:10:42,145 --> 00:10:43,104
But him?

185
00:10:43,224 --> 00:10:44,344
He counts poker cards.

186
00:10:44,344 --> 00:10:45,344
And he fails.

187
00:10:48,224 --> 00:10:49,864
Wait. Come on.

188
00:10:57,385 --> 00:10:59,145
Rest assured,
we're following up on this.

189
00:10:59,145 --> 00:11:01,224
838747.

190
00:11:01,785 --> 00:11:02,785
I've spoken to him.

191
00:11:03,984 --> 00:11:05,305
I'll double-check it.

192
00:11:07,824 --> 00:11:08,785
I'll email you later.

193
00:11:20,905 --> 00:11:22,344
Don't let a client drink alone.

194
00:11:23,744 --> 00:11:25,104
Sir, got five minutes?

195
00:11:27,984 --> 00:11:28,824
Alright.

196
00:11:28,945 --> 00:11:29,744
I'm off.

197
00:11:29,744 --> 00:11:30,265
Go ahead.

198
00:11:35,504 --> 00:11:36,744
Sir, here's the thing.

199
00:11:37,145 --> 00:11:37,945
Last month,

200
00:11:37,945 --> 00:11:39,984
I had a 1.6 million yuan order.

201
00:11:40,145 --> 00:11:41,704
It wasn't credited to me.

202
00:11:41,864 --> 00:11:42,464
Which one?

203
00:11:42,504 --> 00:11:44,072
Zhou Xiaowei from Bingcheng Clothing.

204
00:11:45,984 --> 00:11:47,504
Isn't he your client?

205
00:11:47,504 --> 00:11:48,185
What happened?

206
00:11:48,464 --> 00:11:49,265
Yeah.

207
00:11:49,704 --> 00:11:52,584
He placed the order
under another company's name.

208
00:11:53,104 --> 00:11:53,744
It was credited

209
00:11:53,744 --> 00:11:54,665
to Yu Wei'e.

210
00:11:56,624 --> 00:11:57,385
Company name?

211
00:11:58,104 --> 00:11:59,945
Qichen E-commerce Company.

212
00:11:59,945 --> 00:12:01,824
Qi, as in "orderly".

213
00:12:01,824 --> 00:12:03,224
Chen, as in "morning".

214
00:12:04,624 --> 00:12:05,145
Got it.

215
00:12:06,984 --> 00:12:09,624
This company
falls under Yu Wei'e's territory.

216
00:12:09,624 --> 00:12:10,945
So the credit goes to him.

217
00:12:11,344 --> 00:12:12,464
But that's my client.

218
00:12:13,464 --> 00:12:15,464
You should tell your clients
to place orders

219
00:12:15,464 --> 00:12:16,824
under their names

220
00:12:17,065 --> 00:12:18,104
rather than complain now.

221
00:12:18,464 --> 00:12:19,305
That's not it, sir.

222
00:12:19,624 --> 00:12:22,065
He's placed orders
under company names before.

223
00:12:22,065 --> 00:12:23,305
They were credited to me.

224
00:12:23,824 --> 00:12:26,025
He just used
a different company name this time.

225
00:12:26,145 --> 00:12:27,385
It's the same person.

226
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:29,160
Can't you reassign the credit?

227
00:12:29,385 --> 00:12:30,025
I'm afraid not.

228
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:33,344
Personal and corporate clients
are strictly separate categories.

229
00:12:33,344 --> 00:12:34,265
It's company policy.

230
00:12:34,984 --> 00:12:35,784
Everyone knows that.

231
00:12:36,145 --> 00:12:37,905
I-I know the rules.

232
00:12:37,905 --> 00:12:40,704
But this client
placed the order because of me.

233
00:12:41,145 --> 00:12:42,744
It's a 1.6 million yuan deal, sir.

234
00:12:42,744 --> 00:12:43,504
Please.

235
00:12:43,945 --> 00:12:44,776
Reassign the credit.

236
00:12:45,344 --> 00:12:45,744
I'm sorry.

237
00:12:52,224 --> 00:12:54,504
Alright. Okay.

238
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,536
(Lingyang Industrial, Mr. Shen)

239
00:13:07,112 --> 00:13:08,185
(Lingyang Industrial, Mr. Shen)

240
00:13:08,185 --> 00:13:08,744
Liang.

241
00:13:09,464 --> 00:13:10,265
Free tonight?

242
00:13:10,905 --> 00:13:12,344
I'll introduce you to some friends.

243
00:13:14,344 --> 00:13:15,185
(Friends?)

244
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,504
(Shen Mo's friends
aren't ordinary people.)

245
00:13:20,065 --> 00:13:22,305
(No, no. He's Dong Yue's client.)

246
00:13:24,344 --> 00:13:27,065
(Whatever. An empty stomach
doesn't care about right or wrong.)

247
00:13:27,545 --> 00:13:29,128
(Isn't sales about claiming territory,)

248
00:13:29,584 --> 00:13:30,864
(even if it's Dong Yue's.)

249
00:13:31,265 --> 00:13:34,425
(His client came to me. Go for it.)

250
00:13:40,984 --> 00:13:41,344
Mr. Li.

251
00:13:41,824 --> 00:13:43,744
- No need. I'm not cold.
- Yes, you are.

252
00:13:44,464 --> 00:13:45,545
I'm not drunk.

253
00:13:46,224 --> 00:13:47,385
I'm not drunk.

254
00:13:50,385 --> 00:13:51,464
Yu, go back to drink.

255
00:13:51,905 --> 00:13:52,744
Mr. Li.

256
00:13:52,744 --> 00:13:53,265
I'm fine.

257
00:13:53,504 --> 00:13:54,104
The car's here.

258
00:13:54,425 --> 00:13:55,545
Wait. I'll walk you out.

259
00:13:55,785 --> 00:13:56,385
Mr. Li.

260
00:13:58,065 --> 00:14:01,704
Don't you want some premium,
limited-edition liquor?

261
00:14:01,984 --> 00:14:03,104
She handles VIP clients.

262
00:14:03,224 --> 00:14:04,025
Ask her.

263
00:14:04,464 --> 00:14:06,265
What perks do VIPs get?

264
00:14:06,265 --> 00:14:09,305
VIP status
is exclusively for our members.

265
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:12,425
Our company sells limited-edition liquor

266
00:14:12,744 --> 00:14:13,945
to our VIPs.

267
00:14:14,104 --> 00:14:16,104
A certain liquor
may have as few as 50 bottles,

268
00:14:16,704 --> 00:14:17,744
unavailable on the market.

269
00:14:17,744 --> 00:14:18,665
But through me,

270
00:14:19,305 --> 00:14:20,104
you can get them.

271
00:14:21,425 --> 00:14:22,185
That's perfect.

272
00:14:22,385 --> 00:14:23,464
I absolutely need this.

273
00:14:23,624 --> 00:14:24,704
Absolutely.

274
00:14:25,104 --> 00:14:26,504
Add her on WeChat.

275
00:14:26,504 --> 00:14:27,145
Come on.

276
00:14:27,145 --> 00:14:27,785
Come on.

277
00:14:28,265 --> 00:14:28,744
Ms. Liang.

278
00:14:28,744 --> 00:14:29,504
- Thank you, Mr. Shen.
- Come on.

279
00:14:29,624 --> 00:14:30,984
Let me add all you gentlemen.

280
00:14:30,984 --> 00:14:31,945
Let me do it.

281
00:14:32,025 --> 00:14:33,185
Alright, here.

282
00:14:33,824 --> 00:14:34,945
Thanks. Add me too.

283
00:14:35,065 --> 00:14:36,824
This isn't a payment QR code, is it?

284
00:14:37,104 --> 00:14:38,104
No, no.

285
00:14:38,265 --> 00:14:38,905
Rest assured.

286
00:14:38,905 --> 00:14:39,744
Come on.

287
00:14:40,104 --> 00:14:41,385
Make sure you buy from her.

288
00:14:41,704 --> 00:14:42,305
Absolutely.

289
00:14:45,265 --> 00:14:45,785
Want a drink?

290
00:14:46,945 --> 00:14:47,704
Let's sing.

291
00:14:47,945 --> 00:14:48,872
What Is Life All About?

292
00:14:49,224 --> 00:14:50,464
What Is Life All About?

293
00:14:50,704 --> 00:14:51,265
Okay?

294
00:14:51,545 --> 00:14:52,624
You got it, buddy.

295
00:14:52,624 --> 00:14:53,224
- Okay.
- Come on.

296
00:14:53,704 --> 00:14:55,145
Come on.

297
00:14:55,744 --> 00:14:56,704
Over here.

298
00:14:57,185 --> 00:14:58,104
I need to take this.

299
00:14:58,224 --> 00:14:58,584
Okay.

300
00:14:58,584 --> 00:14:59,864
Go ahead. I need to take this.

301
00:14:59,864 --> 00:15:00,344
Okay.

302
00:15:00,984 --> 00:15:02,065
- Hurry.
- Come on.

303
00:15:02,065 --> 00:15:02,704
Where are you?

304
00:15:03,265 --> 00:15:03,945
Look behind you.

305
00:15:09,624 --> 00:15:10,464
Small world.

306
00:15:10,584 --> 00:15:11,984
You're also here?

307
00:15:14,344 --> 00:15:16,464
You're drinking with Shen Mo?

308
00:15:17,864 --> 00:15:18,545
Why?

309
00:15:19,464 --> 00:15:21,265
Don't you know he's Mr. Dong's client?

310
00:15:22,376 --> 00:15:23,464
What are you trying to say?

311
00:15:23,824 --> 00:15:25,704
Playing dumb, huh?

312
00:15:26,104 --> 00:15:27,744
You've got some nerve.

313
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:30,025
How dare you poach Mr. Dong's client?

314
00:15:30,152 --> 00:15:31,864
Didn't you get enough
from those ten shots?

315
00:15:31,864 --> 00:15:33,145
Want another round?

316
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:35,704
Who do you think you are?
Yapping at me all day long.

317
00:15:36,305 --> 00:15:38,025
Who says I'm poaching Mr. Dong's client?

318
00:15:39,504 --> 00:15:40,744
Insult me all you want.

319
00:15:41,464 --> 00:15:44,104
But don't question Mr. Dong's ability
to manage clients.

320
00:15:46,224 --> 00:15:48,665
How do you know he didn't send me?

321
00:15:49,104 --> 00:15:50,065
Let's take a step back.

322
00:15:50,344 --> 00:15:51,344
Why do you care

323
00:15:51,344 --> 00:15:52,104
who I drink with

324
00:15:52,104 --> 00:15:53,104
and whose client I poach?

325
00:15:53,104 --> 00:15:54,584
It's none of your business.

326
00:15:54,984 --> 00:15:55,984
- Get Shen Mo for me.
- Young Miss.

327
00:15:56,464 --> 00:15:57,344
Young Miss.

328
00:15:57,344 --> 00:15:59,104
- Where is he?
- Let me inform him.

329
00:15:59,104 --> 00:15:59,824
Where is Shen Mo?

330
00:15:59,984 --> 00:16:01,224
- Young Miss.
- Inform him what?

331
00:16:01,504 --> 00:16:01,984
Go away.

332
00:16:02,464 --> 00:16:03,145
Shen Mo.

333
00:16:03,905 --> 00:16:04,545
What?

334
00:16:04,744 --> 00:16:06,104
His wife is here.

335
00:16:06,104 --> 00:16:07,425
Are you asking for trouble?

336
00:16:07,905 --> 00:16:09,864
Did fake liquor rot your brain?

337
00:16:09,864 --> 00:16:11,584
Why are you drinking all the time?

338
00:16:11,864 --> 00:16:12,624
Who is this woman?

339
00:16:13,065 --> 00:16:13,624
Who are you?

340
00:16:13,624 --> 00:16:14,305
Get lost.

341
00:16:14,305 --> 00:16:15,265
What's wrong with you?

342
00:16:16,905 --> 00:16:18,624
Get out.

343
00:16:18,624 --> 00:16:19,785
Mr. Zhang, I'm sorry.

344
00:16:19,785 --> 00:16:20,905
Why should I leave?

345
00:16:20,905 --> 00:16:21,744
Sorry about this.

346
00:16:22,104 --> 00:16:23,145
Mr. Wang, I'm sorry.

347
00:16:23,145 --> 00:16:24,344
Get them all out.

348
00:16:24,344 --> 00:16:25,545
Sorry.

349
00:16:25,545 --> 00:16:26,305
I'm so sorry.

350
00:16:26,305 --> 00:16:26,864
Get out.

351
00:16:26,864 --> 00:16:27,385
See you.

352
00:16:27,385 --> 00:16:28,305
- So sorry.
- Sorry.

353
00:16:28,305 --> 00:16:29,305
Are you insane?

354
00:16:29,305 --> 00:16:29,832
Let's go.

355
00:16:30,624 --> 00:16:31,704
You're crossing the line.

356
00:16:32,905 --> 00:16:34,185
I don't know.

357
00:16:34,665 --> 00:16:35,265
You know...

358
00:16:35,265 --> 00:16:35,785
Mike.

359
00:16:36,265 --> 00:16:36,905
Mike.

360
00:16:37,864 --> 00:16:39,104
Don't let anyone through.

361
00:16:39,305 --> 00:16:39,624
Got it.

362
00:16:40,824 --> 00:16:42,305
Get out.

363
00:16:43,065 --> 00:16:44,104
You old man.

364
00:16:44,425 --> 00:16:45,385
You old geezer.

365
00:16:45,665 --> 00:16:46,224
Enough.

366
00:16:46,224 --> 00:16:47,305
Get away.

367
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:48,265
Please, Young Miss.

368
00:16:48,265 --> 00:16:49,425
I hope he dies.

369
00:16:49,744 --> 00:16:51,504
I'll come and make a scene every day

370
00:16:51,504 --> 00:16:52,624
if he doesn't pay up.

371
00:16:54,305 --> 00:16:55,224
I hope he dies.

372
00:17:01,464 --> 00:17:02,065
Andy.

373
00:17:02,464 --> 00:17:04,984
Mr. Shen's girlfriend
has quite the temper.

374
00:17:06,744 --> 00:17:07,945
That's not his girlfriend.

375
00:17:08,464 --> 00:17:10,385
What kind of girlfriend yells like that?

376
00:17:11,105 --> 00:17:11,704
Young Miss.

377
00:17:11,984 --> 00:17:12,984
Mr. Shen's daughter?

378
00:17:13,224 --> 00:17:14,345
So harsh with her dad?

379
00:17:14,585 --> 00:17:16,185
How come we've never seen her before?

380
00:17:18,064 --> 00:17:20,328
She's not decent.
Mr. Shen didn't mention her to others.

381
00:17:22,464 --> 00:17:23,744
Danning, I'm so sorry.

382
00:17:23,744 --> 00:17:24,665
Things got a bit messy.

383
00:17:25,224 --> 00:17:26,105
He has heart problems.

384
00:17:26,105 --> 00:17:27,704
Let him rest. I'll tend to the guests.

385
00:17:27,704 --> 00:17:29,224
Go ahead. Hurry.

386
00:17:29,224 --> 00:17:29,744
Andy.

387
00:17:30,744 --> 00:17:31,224
Over here.

388
00:18:23,704 --> 00:18:24,224
Mr. Shen.

389
00:18:26,224 --> 00:18:26,865
Mr. Shen.

390
00:18:28,464 --> 00:18:28,984
What's wrong?

391
00:18:29,984 --> 00:18:30,345
Nothing.

392
00:18:30,464 --> 00:18:33,024
You didn't come out, so I got worried.

393
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:34,504
I'll get my coat. Bye.

394
00:18:42,544 --> 00:18:43,464
Got any plans later?

395
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:51,105
I actually enjoy taking walks,

396
00:18:52,304 --> 00:18:53,345
especially at this hour.

397
00:18:55,544 --> 00:18:56,224
Empty street.

398
00:18:57,064 --> 00:18:58,185
Walking slowly alone

399
00:18:58,784 --> 00:19:00,585
is quiet and cozy.

400
00:19:01,504 --> 00:19:02,145
I see.

401
00:19:02,385 --> 00:19:03,464
Sorry, I'll leave now.

402
00:19:05,544 --> 00:19:06,665
That's not what I meant.

403
00:19:06,905 --> 00:19:08,145
I know. I was joking.

404
00:19:10,264 --> 00:19:12,425
How long have you been at GST?

405
00:19:12,865 --> 00:19:13,704
For ten years.

406
00:19:15,024 --> 00:19:15,665
Old-timer.

407
00:19:16,865 --> 00:19:19,345
You used to work under Xiang Lin?

408
00:19:20,345 --> 00:19:20,905
Yeah.

409
00:19:21,704 --> 00:19:23,585
I started in promotions,

410
00:19:23,585 --> 00:19:25,264
and then moved to sales for nightclubs.

411
00:19:25,784 --> 00:19:27,224
I've worked under many superiors.

412
00:19:28,024 --> 00:19:30,185
Before Xiang Lin, it was Zhou.

413
00:19:30,185 --> 00:19:31,825
And before that, Zuo.

414
00:19:33,105 --> 00:19:35,224
Anyway, I've had tons of superiors.

415
00:19:38,185 --> 00:19:40,105
Have you ever thought about moving up?

416
00:19:41,425 --> 00:19:42,224
I'm not qualified.

417
00:19:43,425 --> 00:19:45,640
My education and language skills
are both pretty basic.

418
00:19:46,504 --> 00:19:48,704
But honestly, I never wanted to move up.

419
00:19:49,264 --> 00:19:51,984
Workplace politics is too complicated.

420
00:19:52,145 --> 00:19:53,264
I'm fine where I am.

421
00:19:53,945 --> 00:19:55,905
I just focus on doing my own job well.

422
00:19:56,145 --> 00:19:57,665
My superiors don't need to intervene.

423
00:19:59,064 --> 00:20:00,984
Dong Yue once asked me about you.

424
00:20:01,865 --> 00:20:02,625
Right?

425
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:06,345
It's like this with every new boss.

426
00:20:06,984 --> 00:20:08,105
They've all heard rumors.

427
00:20:08,105 --> 00:20:11,024
A woman like me
selling liquor in nightclubs

428
00:20:11,464 --> 00:20:12,865
must have slept my way up

429
00:20:12,865 --> 00:20:13,905
with many people.

430
00:20:14,224 --> 00:20:15,345
They're all so curious,

431
00:20:15,704 --> 00:20:16,865
but too scared to ask me.

432
00:20:16,865 --> 00:20:19,704
So they just ask around.
Eventually, I got smarter.

433
00:20:19,984 --> 00:20:21,105
I go straight to talk

434
00:20:21,185 --> 00:20:22,544
to my new bosses.

435
00:20:23,224 --> 00:20:23,704
About what?

436
00:20:25,064 --> 00:20:25,704
I just say,

437
00:20:26,385 --> 00:20:26,905
"Sir,

438
00:20:27,145 --> 00:20:28,304
let's not talk work today.

439
00:20:28,625 --> 00:20:30,064
Feel free to ask anything

440
00:20:30,064 --> 00:20:32,264
you want to know about me.

441
00:20:32,264 --> 00:20:34,145
But let me make three things clear.

442
00:20:34,385 --> 00:20:35,825
First, I don't want a promotion.

443
00:20:36,024 --> 00:20:36,945
So don't worry.

444
00:20:37,064 --> 00:20:39,145
Second, tell me your sales target,

445
00:20:39,145 --> 00:20:40,825
and I'll try my best to hit it.

446
00:20:40,825 --> 00:20:42,825
Third, I've never slept with a client."

447
00:20:45,264 --> 00:20:46,665
You said the same to Dong Yue?

448
00:20:46,905 --> 00:20:47,425
Yeah.

449
00:20:47,425 --> 00:20:48,544
That's what I told him.

450
00:20:49,024 --> 00:20:51,704
He hadn't spoken to me for a month,
as if I scared him.

451
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:54,345
I can tell

452
00:20:55,105 --> 00:20:57,385
that you're not the materialistic type.

453
00:20:58,264 --> 00:20:59,544
I wouldn't say that.

454
00:21:00,185 --> 00:21:01,504
I like nice things,

455
00:21:01,504 --> 00:21:03,784
but only if the cost to get them
isn't too high.

456
00:21:04,905 --> 00:21:08,744
You know, I'm not a young girl anymore.

457
00:21:09,304 --> 00:21:11,304
I know. You have a daughter.

458
00:21:11,905 --> 00:21:12,905
How did you know that?

459
00:21:14,024 --> 00:21:15,105
I asked around.

460
00:21:17,105 --> 00:21:17,625
Okay.

461
00:21:18,504 --> 00:21:20,905
I have an adorable little girl

462
00:21:21,345 --> 00:21:22,304
in elementary school.

463
00:21:24,064 --> 00:21:24,825
You married early.

464
00:21:25,984 --> 00:21:26,865
I married early, too.

465
00:21:28,464 --> 00:21:31,464
I had my daughter in my early twenties.

466
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:34,105
You two must be close in age.

467
00:21:35,464 --> 00:21:37,105
I'm definitely much older than her.

468
00:21:38,064 --> 00:21:39,464
Probably not that much older.

469
00:21:40,665 --> 00:21:42,064
But you're much more mature.

470
00:21:43,665 --> 00:21:44,784
She's 28 now,

471
00:21:45,504 --> 00:21:46,385
yet still so immature.

472
00:21:47,865 --> 00:21:50,625
She's a grown-up,
but has never had a proper job.

473
00:21:51,425 --> 00:21:54,544
She thinks money just falls
from the sky.

474
00:21:55,345 --> 00:21:56,425
If I were your daughter,

475
00:21:56,425 --> 00:21:57,345
I'd be so upset.

476
00:21:57,385 --> 00:21:59,064
You've just revealed my age.

477
00:22:06,544 --> 00:22:07,945
We've circled back.

478
00:22:08,504 --> 00:22:09,825
You picked a nice spot.

479
00:22:09,825 --> 00:22:11,185
It's such a nice area.

480
00:22:13,425 --> 00:22:14,704
I have a gift for you.

481
00:22:17,504 --> 00:22:18,865
You have it on you?

482
00:22:18,945 --> 00:22:19,704
Open it.

483
00:22:23,784 --> 00:22:24,665
This is too valuable.

484
00:22:24,665 --> 00:22:25,425
I can't accept it.

485
00:22:27,425 --> 00:22:29,504
It's not valuable at all.

486
00:22:30,385 --> 00:22:31,464
Just well-designed.

487
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:33,744
Look.

488
00:22:36,145 --> 00:22:37,160
Let me put it on you.

489
00:22:39,425 --> 00:22:40,984
Thank you.

490
00:22:46,105 --> 00:22:46,865
Wait.

491
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:47,945
Need some light?

492
00:22:49,784 --> 00:22:52,105
My eyesight is getting worse.

493
00:22:52,504 --> 00:22:53,185
No.

494
00:22:53,185 --> 00:22:54,865
It's just too dark here.

495
00:22:56,585 --> 00:22:57,704
Almost done.

496
00:22:57,905 --> 00:22:58,568
Hang in there.

497
00:23:02,696 --> 00:23:03,304
There you go.

498
00:23:06,185 --> 00:23:07,704
What a lovely bracelet.

499
00:23:07,945 --> 00:23:08,744
I really like it.

500
00:23:09,665 --> 00:23:10,665
I really like you too.

501
00:23:13,625 --> 00:23:14,464
So straightforward?

502
00:23:15,945 --> 00:23:16,865
I'm not young anymore.

503
00:23:17,504 --> 00:23:19,744
That's why I prefer being direct.

504
00:23:21,064 --> 00:23:22,825
But you're way too direct.

505
00:23:22,825 --> 00:23:24,544
I don't know how to respond.

506
00:23:26,064 --> 00:23:27,905
That's what I like about you.

507
00:23:28,304 --> 00:23:29,544
You always make me happy.

508
00:23:32,185 --> 00:23:34,224
If you promise not to say scary things

509
00:23:34,585 --> 00:23:36,064
like that again,

510
00:23:36,064 --> 00:23:37,625
I'll keep making you happy.

511
00:23:37,784 --> 00:23:38,345
Scary?

512
00:23:38,784 --> 00:23:39,865
Did I scare you?

513
00:23:44,185 --> 00:23:45,905
I-I need to go home.

514
00:23:46,784 --> 00:23:48,328
I'll have the driver take you back.

515
00:23:49,224 --> 00:23:50,304
Where are we going?

516
00:23:50,865 --> 00:23:51,625
Home.

517
00:23:51,945 --> 00:23:52,744
No.

518
00:23:52,945 --> 00:23:53,744
Take Ms. Liang home.

519
00:23:53,744 --> 00:23:55,105
- I'm not going home.
- Why did you drink so much?

520
00:23:56,024 --> 00:23:56,865
What about you?

521
00:23:56,905 --> 00:23:57,744
I told you to drink less.

522
00:23:57,744 --> 00:23:58,625
I can manage.

523
00:23:59,105 --> 00:23:59,585
Mr. Shen.

524
00:24:01,264 --> 00:24:01,865
Mr. Dong?

525
00:24:02,865 --> 00:24:03,704
Shen Xing is drunk.

526
00:24:03,704 --> 00:24:04,544
I'll take her home.

527
00:24:05,704 --> 00:24:07,385
I'll come and make a scene every day

528
00:24:07,385 --> 00:24:08,504
if he doesn't pay up.

529
00:24:11,984 --> 00:24:15,105
He's dating
a young and beautiful rich girl.

530
00:24:15,105 --> 00:24:15,784
Young Miss.

531
00:24:15,905 --> 00:24:16,825
Mr. Shen's daughter?

532
00:24:17,264 --> 00:24:17,825
Go ahead.

533
00:24:18,385 --> 00:24:19,704
Who is she?

534
00:24:20,425 --> 00:24:21,345
Who is she?

535
00:24:23,064 --> 00:24:24,024
- Who is she?
- Watch the road.

536
00:24:24,024 --> 00:24:24,825
Watch the road.

537
00:24:25,585 --> 00:24:26,345
Go ahead.

538
00:24:32,024 --> 00:24:32,784
(I'm Dong Yue,)

539
00:24:33,744 --> 00:24:36,425
(the youngest Deputy Sales Director
at GST China.)

540
00:24:37,385 --> 00:24:38,865
(I reached this position)

541
00:24:39,464 --> 00:24:43,024
(thanks to support of Shen Mo,
our largest distributor.)

542
00:24:44,064 --> 00:24:45,585
(And Shen Mo supports me)

543
00:24:45,585 --> 00:24:47,304
(because my performance is top-notch)

544
00:24:47,304 --> 00:24:48,784
(and my skills are unmatched.)

545
00:24:49,665 --> 00:24:50,224
Let's go home.

546
00:24:50,905 --> 00:24:51,865
(Of course not.)

547
00:24:53,304 --> 00:24:54,704
(Those are important factors.)

548
00:24:55,504 --> 00:24:57,024
(But the real reason is)

549
00:24:57,024 --> 00:25:00,625
(that Shen Mo's only daughter,
Shen Xing, is my girlfriend.)

550
00:25:01,945 --> 00:25:02,744
(About this,)

551
00:25:03,385 --> 00:25:06,345
(I, Shen Mo, and Shen Xing,)

552
00:25:07,145 --> 00:25:08,464
(have reached a consensus.)

553
00:25:10,425 --> 00:25:14,385
(You probably think
I'm just freeloading off connections.)

554
00:25:16,185 --> 00:25:18,064
(I'm not building rockets.)

555
00:25:18,385 --> 00:25:20,544
(Sales is all about relationships.)

556
00:25:21,464 --> 00:25:22,905
(What's wrong with a nepotism hire?)

557
00:25:25,945 --> 00:25:28,825
(It's fine as long as
it boosts my sales performance.)

558
00:25:29,704 --> 00:25:30,304
(Besides,)

559
00:25:31,425 --> 00:25:33,665
(Young Miss loves me.)

560
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:34,665
What do you mean?

561
00:25:35,024 --> 00:25:36,425
"You've worked hard."

562
00:25:37,625 --> 00:25:39,665
So fake, just like my dad.

563
00:25:41,704 --> 00:25:44,264
Do not act like my dad.

564
00:25:44,945 --> 00:25:46,105
Okay, I won't be like him.

565
00:25:47,024 --> 00:25:48,544
Then why did you go to him today?

566
00:25:50,064 --> 00:25:51,024
Liu Ying.

567
00:25:52,224 --> 00:25:53,024
Your bestie?

568
00:25:54,024 --> 00:25:55,504
Not anymore.

569
00:25:56,385 --> 00:25:57,865
My dad wants to date her.

570
00:25:57,865 --> 00:25:59,825
He gave her a VIP card for Cocoon.

571
00:25:59,984 --> 00:26:01,744
She even flaunted it on social media,

572
00:26:02,544 --> 00:26:03,665
as if I were dead.

573
00:26:04,585 --> 00:26:05,504
I warned her.

574
00:26:05,504 --> 00:26:07,024
If she dares to date my dad,

575
00:26:07,024 --> 00:26:09,504
I'll take her down with me.

576
00:26:09,504 --> 00:26:10,464
Yeah.

577
00:26:10,945 --> 00:26:11,585
Stand straight.

578
00:26:11,905 --> 00:26:12,665
Don't fall.

579
00:26:16,504 --> 00:26:18,784
If I weren't Shen Mo's daughter,

580
00:26:20,064 --> 00:26:21,704
would you still love me?

581
00:26:22,145 --> 00:26:23,345
Of course I would.

582
00:26:26,024 --> 00:26:29,264
P-Prove it to me.

583
00:26:29,425 --> 00:26:30,425
How should I prove it?

584
00:26:30,425 --> 00:26:31,688
Should I jump off your balcony?

585
00:26:33,585 --> 00:26:35,464
Your balcony works too.

586
00:26:35,464 --> 00:26:36,464
Fine, I'll jump.

587
00:26:41,704 --> 00:26:42,665
We're home.

588
00:26:43,345 --> 00:26:43,865
Hold me.

589
00:26:43,865 --> 00:26:44,784
I'm holding you.

590
00:26:45,905 --> 00:26:46,744
We're home.

591
00:26:48,105 --> 00:26:49,425
Alright, we're home. Lie down.

592
00:26:50,385 --> 00:26:51,024
Wait here.

593
00:26:51,224 --> 00:26:52,744
No, I want more.

594
00:26:53,345 --> 00:26:54,024
Alright.

595
00:26:54,024 --> 00:26:54,865
But I told you.

596
00:26:54,865 --> 00:26:56,145
Don't bite me. It hurts.

597
00:26:56,704 --> 00:26:57,504
I won't bite.

598
00:26:57,504 --> 00:27:00,224
Come and shower with me, okay?

599
00:27:00,224 --> 00:27:01,865
Listen to me. Get a shower yourself.

600
00:27:02,024 --> 00:27:03,544
I'll get you some lemon water, okay?

601
00:27:03,744 --> 00:27:05,945
- You'll feel better.
- No, don't go.

602
00:27:05,945 --> 00:27:06,704
You're back.

603
00:27:07,425 --> 00:27:08,304
Ms. Zhang, we're back.

604
00:27:09,064 --> 00:27:11,464
- Don't go.
- She's drunk again?

605
00:27:11,905 --> 00:27:13,064
Please watch her. I'll leave.

606
00:27:13,064 --> 00:27:13,665
Seriously.

607
00:27:14,185 --> 00:27:15,905
- Hurry.
- You're the drunk one.

608
00:27:16,145 --> 00:27:16,984
I'm not drunk.

609
00:27:16,984 --> 00:27:18,744
Yeah, I am drunk.

610
00:27:18,744 --> 00:27:19,385
Let's go.

611
00:27:20,024 --> 00:27:20,984
Take a shower.

612
00:27:21,385 --> 00:27:23,145
Go to sleep. Let's go.

613
00:27:24,504 --> 00:27:25,665
It's so late.

614
00:27:26,464 --> 00:27:27,625
Stop drinking so much.

615
00:27:27,625 --> 00:27:29,905
Sweetie, I'll wait for you.

616
00:27:31,105 --> 00:27:31,945
Hurry up.

617
00:27:32,464 --> 00:27:33,224
Come on, lie down.

618
00:27:49,345 --> 00:27:51,345
She fell asleep instantly.

619
00:27:52,024 --> 00:27:53,665
Is the rice cake from my mom?

620
00:27:54,064 --> 00:27:54,825
I think so.

621
00:27:57,105 --> 00:27:57,905
I'm not sure.

622
00:27:58,304 --> 00:27:59,224
I'll go get a basin.

623
00:27:59,984 --> 00:28:01,504
She might throw up.

624
00:28:17,585 --> 00:28:18,105
Your boss

625
00:28:18,345 --> 00:28:19,224
is stuck in traffic?

626
00:28:20,264 --> 00:28:20,865
Sorry.

627
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:21,585
I was busy

628
00:28:21,585 --> 00:28:22,585
and forgot to tell you.

629
00:28:22,585 --> 00:28:23,544
My boss is here.

630
00:28:23,825 --> 00:28:26,145
Some suppliers and peers are with him.

631
00:28:26,145 --> 00:28:28,185
He'll come to keep you company
once they leave.

632
00:28:29,064 --> 00:28:30,264
Is he avoiding me?

633
00:28:30,304 --> 00:28:30,825
No.

634
00:28:30,825 --> 00:28:31,585
Not at all.

635
00:28:31,945 --> 00:28:34,024
I'll look for him again.

636
00:28:37,744 --> 00:28:38,544
No weaseling out.

637
00:28:38,544 --> 00:28:40,304
Bottoms up.
Everyone, bottoms up!

638
00:28:40,865 --> 00:28:41,464
No tricks.

639
00:28:43,064 --> 00:28:43,704
Bottoms up.

640
00:28:44,704 --> 00:28:45,425
Go with Andy.

641
00:28:46,145 --> 00:28:47,304
See if Shen is around.

642
00:28:47,464 --> 00:28:48,024
If he is,

643
00:28:48,665 --> 00:28:50,665
tell him to front
another 3,000 cases of Gennadiy.

644
00:28:54,472 --> 00:28:55,016
(Purchase Contract)

645
00:29:02,064 --> 00:29:03,585
We still have many left.

646
00:29:04,744 --> 00:29:05,984
Another 3,000 cases?

647
00:29:07,825 --> 00:29:09,264
Xu Yuntian makes it sound easy.

648
00:29:09,544 --> 00:29:11,744
I've paid you tens of millions.

649
00:29:12,345 --> 00:29:14,345
Tell him to come see my warehouse.

650
00:29:14,825 --> 00:29:16,905
The previous shipments
haven't even sold.

651
00:29:16,905 --> 00:29:18,464
They are filling the whole place.

652
00:29:19,784 --> 00:29:21,665
You're dumping it all on us

653
00:29:21,665 --> 00:29:22,585
just to impress

654
00:29:22,825 --> 00:29:23,825
the headquarters.

655
00:29:26,585 --> 00:29:29,024
Do you know
how little I make per bottle?

656
00:29:29,984 --> 00:29:32,345
It doesn't even cover the storage fees.

657
00:29:33,304 --> 00:29:34,464
Getting drunk...

658
00:29:34,464 --> 00:29:36,024
You think I don't need cash?

659
00:29:36,385 --> 00:29:37,345
That's impressive.

660
00:29:37,585 --> 00:29:38,504
Xu Yuntian.

661
00:29:38,504 --> 00:29:39,464
It's not that simple.

662
00:29:39,825 --> 00:29:41,665
Treating me as a piggy bank.

663
00:29:41,665 --> 00:29:42,926
(Shen Mo)

664
00:29:44,145 --> 00:29:44,704
Mr. Shen.

665
00:29:46,744 --> 00:29:47,345
I'm sorry

666
00:29:48,264 --> 00:29:48,984
about this.

667
00:29:49,704 --> 00:29:50,744
It's a real headache.

668
00:29:50,744 --> 00:29:51,688
It's not your fault.

669
00:29:52,425 --> 00:29:53,744
Xu Yuntian got carried away.

670
00:29:53,784 --> 00:29:54,825
You're still young.

671
00:29:54,865 --> 00:29:56,224
There's still a lot to learn.

672
00:29:57,625 --> 00:29:58,704
But it's okay.

673
00:29:59,024 --> 00:30:00,425
You're young after all.

674
00:30:00,425 --> 00:30:01,784
You have opportunities.

675
00:30:03,304 --> 00:30:04,224
Come on, cheers.

676
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:04,744
Come on.

677
00:30:04,744 --> 00:30:05,064
Cheers.

678
00:30:05,064 --> 00:30:05,665
Cheers.

679
00:30:08,905 --> 00:30:09,984
Here's a story.

680
00:30:10,905 --> 00:30:13,504
Twenty years ago,
there was a big shot in Foshan.

681
00:30:14,704 --> 00:30:15,464
This guy

682
00:30:16,185 --> 00:30:17,905
was only about this tall,

683
00:30:18,744 --> 00:30:20,945
and his waist was this thick.

684
00:30:21,544 --> 00:30:23,784
He looked just like a mahjong tile.

685
00:30:25,224 --> 00:30:25,984
One day,

686
00:30:26,145 --> 00:30:28,105
we were having a late-night snack.

687
00:30:28,304 --> 00:30:30,504
He showed up with a few thugs.

688
00:30:32,024 --> 00:30:33,385
He saw us from far away.

689
00:30:34,024 --> 00:30:34,704
And

690
00:30:34,704 --> 00:30:36,185
he spread his arms.

691
00:30:37,145 --> 00:30:38,064
You know?

692
00:30:38,464 --> 00:30:41,825
Back then, people loved
tucking a bag under their arms.

693
00:30:42,264 --> 00:30:43,625
He grabbed his bag.

694
00:30:44,185 --> 00:30:45,345
Without thinking

695
00:30:45,625 --> 00:30:46,625
and looking,

696
00:30:47,145 --> 00:30:48,224
he tossed it into the air.

697
00:30:48,945 --> 00:30:49,504
Why?

698
00:30:50,784 --> 00:30:52,024
We were stunned.

699
00:30:52,504 --> 00:30:54,224
We wondered where he'd throw the bag.

700
00:30:54,744 --> 00:30:56,464
Then a thug rushed out from behind him

701
00:30:57,464 --> 00:30:59,784
like a martial arts master.

702
00:31:00,345 --> 00:31:00,865
He leaped

703
00:31:01,345 --> 00:31:02,185
and grabbed the bag

704
00:31:03,064 --> 00:31:04,385
with one hand.

705
00:31:04,385 --> 00:31:05,224
Impressive.

706
00:31:05,625 --> 00:31:07,145
Did they rehearse this many times?

707
00:31:07,425 --> 00:31:08,304
Of course.

708
00:31:08,585 --> 00:31:10,345
Otherwise, how could he catch it?

709
00:31:12,185 --> 00:31:13,425
Do you want to know

710
00:31:13,704 --> 00:31:15,704
who that thug is?

711
00:31:20,504 --> 00:31:22,145
Let me show you. Come on.

712
00:31:22,224 --> 00:31:22,945
Okay.

713
00:31:22,945 --> 00:31:23,464
Here.

714
00:31:23,464 --> 00:31:23,865
Let's go.

715
00:31:26,544 --> 00:31:26,952
Come on.

716
00:31:27,224 --> 00:31:28,185
Come on.

717
00:31:28,185 --> 00:31:29,585
Come on.

718
00:31:29,744 --> 00:31:30,345
Take a look.

719
00:31:30,945 --> 00:31:32,865
That's the one. See?

720
00:31:42,665 --> 00:31:43,385
Can't tell, huh?

721
00:31:44,185 --> 00:31:45,625
He knows kung fu.

722
00:31:46,304 --> 00:31:47,024
Kung fu?

723
00:31:47,024 --> 00:31:47,464
Yeah.

724
00:31:48,865 --> 00:31:50,105
Dong Yue, get back to work.

725
00:31:59,224 --> 00:32:01,625
Mr. Shen, Tommy's gone
to persuade that girl.

726
00:32:01,625 --> 00:32:02,464
Now we'll see

727
00:32:02,464 --> 00:32:03,905
if she dares to propose a toast.

728
00:32:04,185 --> 00:32:05,744
It's fine if she doesn't.

729
00:32:06,425 --> 00:32:08,825
Plenty of beauties will gladly do it.

730
00:32:09,464 --> 00:32:10,224
No, no.

731
00:32:10,224 --> 00:32:11,585
Promoters are not allowed

732
00:32:11,585 --> 00:32:13,304
to drink during work hours

733
00:32:13,304 --> 00:32:14,665
or leave their posts.

734
00:32:15,945 --> 00:32:16,544
Look.

735
00:32:17,585 --> 00:32:18,385
Look.

736
00:32:20,185 --> 00:32:21,464
Zhao Mei's your boss, right?

737
00:32:22,064 --> 00:32:24,385
She was also a sales lady
when she was young.

738
00:32:24,945 --> 00:32:26,504
If she'd been as stubborn as you,

739
00:32:26,504 --> 00:32:27,625
she wouldn't have made it.

740
00:32:28,464 --> 00:32:29,865
What do you think got her here?

741
00:32:30,345 --> 00:32:32,024
Following the rules?

742
00:32:32,185 --> 00:32:33,945
Being invisible to the boss?

743
00:32:34,224 --> 00:32:35,504
Standing around doing nothing?

744
00:32:36,224 --> 00:32:37,185
Young lady.

745
00:32:37,504 --> 00:32:40,145
Mr. Xu hardly comes here.

746
00:32:41,625 --> 00:32:43,185
Seize the opportunity.

747
00:32:43,464 --> 00:32:44,185
You know?

748
00:32:46,345 --> 00:32:49,064
You need to bravely charge

749
00:32:49,264 --> 00:32:50,585
towards the boss.

750
00:33:14,145 --> 00:33:15,264
Mission accomplished?

751
00:33:15,945 --> 00:33:16,665
It's hard.

752
00:33:21,984 --> 00:33:22,425
Long.

753
00:33:23,865 --> 00:33:26,625
The promoter at the door is toasting Xu.

754
00:33:27,145 --> 00:33:28,425
Copy that.

755
00:33:29,585 --> 00:33:30,105
No, no.

756
00:33:30,105 --> 00:33:30,665
Mr. Xu.

757
00:33:31,105 --> 00:33:32,504
May I offer you a toast?

758
00:33:37,145 --> 00:33:37,784
Everything okay?

759
00:33:38,544 --> 00:33:39,544
Don't ruin the vibe.

760
00:33:40,064 --> 00:33:40,984
She's my employee.

761
00:33:46,704 --> 00:33:47,784
Take her place if you want.

762
00:33:49,784 --> 00:33:50,625
Mr. Xu.

763
00:33:51,105 --> 00:33:52,105
Seriously?

764
00:33:52,105 --> 00:33:53,145
Mr. Xu.

765
00:34:36,945 --> 00:34:37,305
Mr. Shen.

766
00:34:38,144 --> 00:34:38,745
Are you home?

767
00:34:39,464 --> 00:34:40,385
Yeah, don't worry.

768
00:34:40,385 --> 00:34:41,504
Shen Xing fell asleep.

769
00:34:41,785 --> 00:34:43,504
I ran into Tang Jianguang from Qilin.

770
00:34:44,184 --> 00:34:45,064
He dodged me.

771
00:34:46,225 --> 00:34:47,385
Tang Jianguang?

772
00:34:48,064 --> 00:34:49,184
He's Mr. Xu's client.

773
00:34:49,184 --> 00:34:50,865
He's been delaying contract renewal.

774
00:34:50,865 --> 00:34:52,865
We need to find out why.

775
00:34:53,225 --> 00:34:54,745
Tang Jianguang orders huge volumes.

776
00:34:55,104 --> 00:34:56,144
We can't lose him.

777
00:34:57,024 --> 00:34:57,584
Don't worry.

778
00:34:57,584 --> 00:34:59,184
I'll follow up tomorrow.

779
00:35:18,624 --> 00:35:19,504
You can't easily

780
00:35:19,745 --> 00:35:21,345
find the tea I have here.

781
00:35:27,225 --> 00:35:27,664
Here.

782
00:35:29,945 --> 00:35:31,265
See those compressed tea cakes?

783
00:35:32,024 --> 00:35:33,224
None costs less than 150,000.

784
00:35:34,305 --> 00:35:34,945
Impressive.

785
00:35:34,945 --> 00:35:36,785
No wonder they say
tea costs more than liquor.

786
00:35:38,385 --> 00:35:39,305
Two different things.

787
00:35:40,504 --> 00:35:42,024
Tea during the day.

788
00:35:42,664 --> 00:35:43,345
Liquor at night.

789
00:35:43,825 --> 00:35:44,584
Why choose

790
00:35:45,104 --> 00:35:46,024
when both are fine?

791
00:35:49,104 --> 00:35:49,785
I know

792
00:35:50,184 --> 00:35:51,425
you came to talk about

793
00:35:52,024 --> 00:35:52,905
contract renewal.

794
00:35:53,584 --> 00:35:54,024
Yeah.

795
00:35:54,945 --> 00:35:55,865
I order liquor

796
00:35:56,265 --> 00:35:58,225
to entertain my friends.

797
00:35:58,905 --> 00:35:59,664
Brand,

798
00:35:59,945 --> 00:36:00,584
quantity,

799
00:36:00,705 --> 00:36:01,305
who orders...

800
00:36:01,624 --> 00:36:02,544
I really don't care.

801
00:36:04,305 --> 00:36:07,905
But I've been friends with Xu Yuntian

802
00:36:08,425 --> 00:36:09,825
for over twenty years.

803
00:36:11,584 --> 00:36:13,785
He's having a hard time.

804
00:36:14,425 --> 00:36:15,184
At this point,

805
00:36:15,425 --> 00:36:18,945
I really should take him seriously,
understand?

806
00:36:19,265 --> 00:36:19,825
Got it.

807
00:36:21,584 --> 00:36:22,385
You're honest.

808
00:36:22,385 --> 00:36:23,464
Let me ask one more thing.

809
00:36:24,104 --> 00:36:26,785
Does Mr. Xu want you to switch brands

810
00:36:26,785 --> 00:36:28,624
or purchase from someone else?

811
00:36:29,905 --> 00:36:31,184
I'm not switching brands.

812
00:36:31,785 --> 00:36:35,104
Xu really has a soft spot for GST.

813
00:36:36,265 --> 00:36:37,104
It's just that

814
00:36:37,385 --> 00:36:38,144
he told me

815
00:36:38,144 --> 00:36:40,905
to place this order with Zhao Mei.

816
00:36:43,945 --> 00:36:44,584
Good.

817
00:36:45,144 --> 00:36:46,504
Since you're still with us,

818
00:36:46,705 --> 00:36:49,905
we can solve the problems
between ourselves.

819
00:36:50,984 --> 00:36:54,144
Mr. Xu gave all the clients to Zhao Mei!

820
00:36:55,064 --> 00:36:57,305
They're coming after our territory.

821
00:36:57,385 --> 00:36:58,705
I can't accept this.

822
00:36:59,225 --> 00:37:01,464
Mr. Xu wants Zhao Mei to take over?

823
00:37:01,464 --> 00:37:02,425
Is he crazy?

824
00:37:02,745 --> 00:37:04,305
A woman as Sales Director?

825
00:37:04,705 --> 00:37:05,504
What's the rush?

826
00:37:06,104 --> 00:37:08,024
Mr. Xu did give clients to Zhao Mei,

827
00:37:08,104 --> 00:37:09,265
but she has to keep them.

828
00:37:09,905 --> 00:37:11,624
What do you mean, sir?

829
00:37:12,745 --> 00:37:14,584
If Tang Jianguang
really listens to Mr. Xu,

830
00:37:14,584 --> 00:37:15,825
why hasn't he signed the deal?

831
00:37:16,305 --> 00:37:17,584
They have been old friends

832
00:37:17,584 --> 00:37:20,024
because Mr. Xu
has been the Sales Director.

833
00:37:20,024 --> 00:37:21,104
He's not anymore.

834
00:37:21,104 --> 00:37:22,705
The brotherhood has soured.

835
00:37:24,024 --> 00:37:24,984
People change.

836
00:37:39,064 --> 00:37:41,064
My place has become a tourist site.

837
00:37:41,584 --> 00:37:43,265
People keep showing up here. Sit.

838
00:37:43,265 --> 00:37:43,825
Okay.

839
00:37:45,425 --> 00:37:46,225
Who else came?

840
00:37:48,024 --> 00:37:48,785
Everyone.

841
00:37:49,385 --> 00:37:50,104
Tang Lide.

842
00:37:51,905 --> 00:37:52,584
Qi Youlan.

843
00:37:52,865 --> 00:37:53,664
Peter Du.

844
00:37:54,825 --> 00:37:55,305
Zhao Mei?

845
00:37:56,345 --> 00:37:56,984
The first.

846
00:37:57,544 --> 00:37:58,584
She has some conscience.

847
00:38:01,225 --> 00:38:01,705
Here.

848
00:38:08,785 --> 00:38:09,425
It's messy here.

849
00:38:10,705 --> 00:38:12,232
My wife took the kids to her parents'.

850
00:38:13,024 --> 00:38:13,984
She wants a divorce.

851
00:38:18,305 --> 00:38:20,104
So, what brings you here?

852
00:38:22,425 --> 00:38:24,984
I met with Tang Jianguang.

853
00:38:26,705 --> 00:38:27,104
Oh?

854
00:38:32,425 --> 00:38:34,305
He said you've been friends
for twenty years.

855
00:38:34,305 --> 00:38:37,104
So the contract renewal
depends on your decision.

856
00:38:38,544 --> 00:38:39,265
He said that?

857
00:38:41,745 --> 00:38:44,664
I'm just a former GST employee.

858
00:38:44,664 --> 00:38:45,624
I hold no power.

859
00:38:46,144 --> 00:38:47,104
I have no say.

860
00:38:49,544 --> 00:38:50,865
You may have left the company,

861
00:38:50,865 --> 00:38:52,064
but everyone respects you,

862
00:38:52,624 --> 00:38:55,865
colleagues and clients alike.

863
00:38:57,305 --> 00:38:59,664
Could you talk to Mr. Tang?

864
00:39:03,104 --> 00:39:04,425
Playing dumb, huh?

865
00:39:04,865 --> 00:39:06,825
I know you want him to sign
with Zhao Mei.

866
00:39:07,584 --> 00:39:08,865
But he hasn't done that.

867
00:39:09,345 --> 00:39:11,865
It means he has his concerns.

868
00:39:14,225 --> 00:39:14,905
Rest assured.

869
00:39:14,905 --> 00:39:16,464
I'll make it worth your while.

870
00:39:16,905 --> 00:39:20,225
Mr. Tang's goods
will go through Lingyang Industrial.

871
00:39:21,624 --> 00:39:24,104
You'll get a one-percent commission.

872
00:39:25,865 --> 00:39:26,825
Lingyang Industrial?

873
00:39:29,104 --> 00:39:31,745
Shen Mo agreed to let you
use his company for kickbacks?

874
00:39:33,144 --> 00:39:34,064
Interesting.

875
00:39:35,265 --> 00:39:36,488
I've settled it with Mr. Shen.

876
00:39:37,664 --> 00:39:38,664
If you don't believe me,

877
00:39:38,664 --> 00:39:40,184
I can call him now.

878
00:39:40,184 --> 00:39:40,624
Do it.

879
00:39:46,144 --> 00:39:47,905
Mr. Shen, Mr. Xu and I...

880
00:39:48,104 --> 00:39:48,745
Okay.

881
00:39:53,345 --> 00:39:54,104
Mr. Shen.

882
00:39:56,624 --> 00:39:58,584
Yeah, Dong Yue is here.

883
00:39:59,984 --> 00:40:00,705
I didn't know

884
00:40:01,225 --> 00:40:02,624
you'd value him so much.

885
00:40:02,825 --> 00:40:03,945
The world is vast.

886
00:40:04,425 --> 00:40:06,664
There are many things you don't know.

887
00:40:07,825 --> 00:40:08,825
If I were you,

888
00:40:09,504 --> 00:40:11,305
I'd take this commission immediately.

889
00:40:12,265 --> 00:40:12,745
Why?

890
00:40:13,785 --> 00:40:15,544
You should take it before it's gone.

891
00:40:16,624 --> 00:40:18,385
Doing this for us
is doing yourself a favor.

892
00:40:19,024 --> 00:40:20,825
You'll gain more opportunities.

893
00:40:21,664 --> 00:40:23,945
Then no one will stand in your way.

894
00:40:25,064 --> 00:40:25,705
Got it.

895
00:40:27,664 --> 00:40:28,865
I'll honor your request.

896
00:40:30,225 --> 00:40:31,624
Alright then.

897
00:40:38,504 --> 00:40:39,785
Interesting.

898
00:40:40,865 --> 00:40:44,024
Do you have something on him?

899
00:40:45,504 --> 00:40:47,865
Or is he really
making you his son-in-law?

900
00:40:56,984 --> 00:40:57,905
But I'm quite curious.

901
00:41:00,544 --> 00:41:02,984
What happens if I refuse?

902
00:41:03,464 --> 00:41:04,305
Nothing much.

903
00:41:05,425 --> 00:41:06,464
If you refuse,

904
00:41:06,785 --> 00:41:09,265
then this commission goes to Mr. Tang.

905
00:41:10,664 --> 00:41:13,024
Since you're ready
to give out one percent,

906
00:41:13,024 --> 00:41:13,984
just approach him.

907
00:41:14,425 --> 00:41:15,584
Mr. Tang is your client.

908
00:41:15,984 --> 00:41:17,425
It's against the rules to bypass you

909
00:41:18,225 --> 00:41:19,064
and contact him.

910
00:41:19,905 --> 00:41:20,345
Rules?

911
00:41:21,305 --> 00:41:21,825
Yeah.

912
00:41:22,504 --> 00:41:23,865
When I first joined GST,

913
00:41:24,544 --> 00:41:26,504
I chose to interview you.

914
00:41:26,504 --> 00:41:27,184
Remember?

915
00:41:27,425 --> 00:41:27,945
Really?

916
00:41:29,825 --> 00:41:32,144
I remember you telling me,

917
00:41:32,385 --> 00:41:33,504
"In this line of work,

918
00:41:33,865 --> 00:41:34,905
you must know the rules.

919
00:41:36,104 --> 00:41:37,064
Otherwise,

920
00:41:37,184 --> 00:41:38,265
you'll fail eventually.

921
00:41:39,305 --> 00:41:40,144
Only those

922
00:41:40,624 --> 00:41:41,825
who follow the rules go far

923
00:41:41,825 --> 00:41:42,624
and soar high."

924
00:41:42,624 --> 00:41:45,345
Now I truly grasp the depth
of that advice.

925
00:41:46,385 --> 00:41:47,385
After all these years,

926
00:41:47,825 --> 00:41:48,544
professionally

927
00:41:48,544 --> 00:41:49,544
and personally,

928
00:41:50,865 --> 00:41:52,425
I've always felt closer to you.

929
00:41:53,825 --> 00:41:55,225
So I prefer that this commission

930
00:41:57,184 --> 00:41:58,345
go to you

931
00:41:59,664 --> 00:42:01,265
rather than Mr. Tang.

932
00:42:05,825 --> 00:42:08,225
No rules, no progress.

933
00:42:20,104 --> 00:42:20,624
Thanks.

934
00:42:23,544 --> 00:42:25,305
Dong Yue, what a coincidence.

935
00:42:25,865 --> 00:42:27,905
Will you be at the office long today?

936
00:42:28,624 --> 00:42:29,945
Depends. Why?

937
00:42:30,265 --> 00:42:32,024
You know the company tradition

938
00:42:32,305 --> 00:42:34,825
where every newbie interviews a senior?

939
00:42:36,104 --> 00:42:37,825
Yeah, I've done that.

940
00:42:38,184 --> 00:42:39,024
Who did you choose?

941
00:42:39,785 --> 00:42:40,425
Mr. Xu.

942
00:42:44,024 --> 00:42:45,345
A newbie chose you today.

943
00:42:46,504 --> 00:42:46,984
Who?

944
00:42:48,144 --> 00:42:48,825
Zeng Zixuan.

945
00:42:54,225 --> 00:42:55,464
Will it take long?

946
00:42:56,584 --> 00:42:57,745
Thirty minutes to an hour.

947
00:43:00,584 --> 00:43:01,464
Come in ten minutes.

948
00:43:01,464 --> 00:43:01,905
Alright.

949
00:43:02,425 --> 00:43:02,905
Thanks.

950
00:43:04,305 --> 00:43:04,745
Done.

951
00:43:05,664 --> 00:43:06,865
I'm heading to Beijing

952
00:43:07,104 --> 00:43:09,305
to meet with an important client.

953
00:43:09,305 --> 00:43:10,064
Just confirmed.

954
00:43:10,064 --> 00:43:10,888
It's this afternoon.

955
00:43:11,705 --> 00:43:13,624
And it's better to lay low.

956
00:43:13,984 --> 00:43:15,624
Layoffs are starting soon.

957
00:43:15,825 --> 00:43:16,504
How soon?

958
00:43:17,345 --> 00:43:18,624
Within half an hour.

959
00:43:19,425 --> 00:43:20,905
I wasn't going to come,

960
00:43:21,305 --> 00:43:23,265
but I couldn't skip
the partners' meeting.

961
00:43:24,184 --> 00:43:25,504
I'll try to return tomorrow.

962
00:43:26,104 --> 00:43:27,464
I'll see Barry again

963
00:43:27,464 --> 00:43:29,144
and push your matter forward.

964
00:43:30,664 --> 00:43:31,785
Thank you.

965
00:43:32,624 --> 00:43:36,184
You're still helping me,
although I almost

966
00:43:36,785 --> 00:43:37,705
ruined your business.

967
00:43:38,504 --> 00:43:39,345
Remember.

968
00:43:39,664 --> 00:43:40,745
We're a married couple

969
00:43:40,905 --> 00:43:42,624
who share a bed.

970
00:43:44,504 --> 00:43:45,825
Thank you, Mr. Li.

971
00:43:49,945 --> 00:43:51,225
Alright, I've got work to do.

972
00:43:51,225 --> 00:43:51,945
Talk later.

973
00:43:52,385 --> 00:43:52,905
Bye.

974
00:43:56,785 --> 00:43:58,385
Why did you join GST?

975
00:43:59,544 --> 00:44:01,265
I interviewed with many companies,

976
00:44:01,265 --> 00:44:02,104
but

977
00:44:02,104 --> 00:44:04,504
GST offered the highest salary
for fresh grads.

978
00:44:06,024 --> 00:44:08,305
What do you love most about GST?

979
00:44:09,865 --> 00:44:10,664
The pay.

980
00:44:12,664 --> 00:44:13,825
GST has many subsidies:

981
00:44:13,825 --> 00:44:15,984
transportation, phone allowance,

982
00:44:15,984 --> 00:44:16,945
and housing stipend.

983
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:19,624
Fresh out of school back then,

984
00:44:19,865 --> 00:44:20,905
all those benefits

985
00:44:20,905 --> 00:44:23,464
were a huge temptation for me.

986
00:44:23,664 --> 00:44:25,064
I found GST amazing.

987
00:44:25,825 --> 00:44:26,664
Later, I realized

988
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:30,345
that those subsidies
were meant for liver supplements.

989
00:44:32,745 --> 00:44:33,945
You got the joke?

990
00:44:34,265 --> 00:44:36,104
The sales staff said it in the store.

991
00:44:37,104 --> 00:44:39,905
So what do you think it takes

992
00:44:40,104 --> 00:44:41,265
to be a good salesperson?

993
00:44:44,184 --> 00:44:45,345
That is too general.

994
00:44:46,385 --> 00:44:48,225
Then what's the most essential quality?

995
00:44:50,144 --> 00:44:50,785
Hunger.

996
00:44:51,745 --> 00:44:53,064
No matter how much they sell,

997
00:44:53,865 --> 00:44:56,024
a good salesperson is never satisfied.

998
00:44:57,865 --> 00:44:58,865
That hunger remains.

999
00:44:59,064 --> 00:44:59,945
Are you like that?

1000
00:44:59,945 --> 00:45:00,865
Never satisfied?

1001
00:45:01,104 --> 00:45:01,865
Of course I am.

1002
00:45:02,584 --> 00:45:03,624
I have a question for you.

1003
00:45:05,104 --> 00:45:05,664
Go ahead.

1004
00:45:06,705 --> 00:45:08,425
Why did you choose to interview me?

1005
00:45:08,825 --> 00:45:11,305
A newcomer would
naturally pick their future boss.

1006
00:45:12,064 --> 00:45:13,104
Theoretically, you should

1007
00:45:14,184 --> 00:45:15,184
interview Zhao Mei.

1008
00:45:17,184 --> 00:45:19,024
Since I'm already on Ms. Zhao's team,

1009
00:45:19,024 --> 00:45:20,825
I have plenty of time to interview her.

1010
00:45:20,825 --> 00:45:22,064
I'll save this opportunity.

1011
00:45:22,825 --> 00:45:25,984
And I want to learn more about sales.

1012
00:45:27,064 --> 00:45:27,624
I see.

1013
00:45:30,584 --> 00:45:31,664
That's about it.

1014
00:45:31,905 --> 00:45:32,664
Thank you, sir.

1015
00:45:33,345 --> 00:45:33,785
No problem.

1016
00:45:34,024 --> 00:45:34,825
I'll head out then.

1017
00:45:41,992 --> 00:45:43,877
(Layoff List)

1018
00:45:45,225 --> 00:45:46,064
Now I'm relieved.

1019
00:45:46,544 --> 00:45:47,624
I'm not getting laid off.

1020
00:45:49,425 --> 00:45:50,216
Thank you, Mr. Li.

1021
00:45:55,024 --> 00:45:55,785
Tao Ling?

1022
00:45:58,425 --> 00:45:59,464
Tao is getting laid off?

1023
00:45:59,825 --> 00:46:00,624
What can we do?

1024
00:46:00,984 --> 00:46:02,225
Every team has to cut staff.

1025
00:46:02,705 --> 00:46:04,225
It's either you or someone else.

1026
00:46:07,865 --> 00:46:09,544
Layoff talks start in ten minutes.

1027
00:46:10,464 --> 00:46:12,785
Don't let others find out
you know the result.

1028
00:46:25,945 --> 00:46:27,104
Got the meeting materials?

1029
00:46:27,544 --> 00:46:28,305
Yeah.

1030
00:46:28,305 --> 00:46:29,265
Let's get going.

1031
00:46:31,624 --> 00:46:32,664
There is a mistake.

1032
00:46:33,905 --> 00:46:34,225
Okay.

1033
00:46:34,385 --> 00:46:35,184
I'll double-check.

1034
00:46:36,144 --> 00:46:37,225
My hand hurts.

1035
00:46:37,705 --> 00:46:39,144
It's tenosynovitis again.

1036
00:46:41,144 --> 00:46:41,705
Hailun.

1037
00:46:42,425 --> 00:46:43,865
Do you still have that spray?

1038
00:46:43,865 --> 00:46:44,785
I really need it.

1039
00:46:45,584 --> 00:46:46,705
- Yeah.
- My hand's killing me.

1040
00:46:48,305 --> 00:46:48,865
Thanks.

1041
00:46:50,785 --> 00:46:51,464
This report

1042
00:46:51,464 --> 00:46:52,544
is due in two days,

1043
00:46:52,865 --> 00:46:54,104
and I'm on the third page.

1044
00:46:54,504 --> 00:46:55,305
Seriously.

1045
00:46:55,504 --> 00:46:56,624
And my wrist is destroyed.

1046
00:46:56,905 --> 00:46:58,064
Why am I so miserable?

1047
00:46:59,425 --> 00:47:00,705
That's nothing.

1048
00:47:00,905 --> 00:47:01,905
I'm the miserable one.

1049
00:47:02,945 --> 00:47:05,624
I'm writing a report
on information security,

1050
00:47:06,425 --> 00:47:07,345
cutting-edge stuff.

1051
00:47:08,104 --> 00:47:09,984
But the problem is, if I really knew

1052
00:47:09,984 --> 00:47:12,064
the cutting-edge
information security stuff,

1053
00:47:12,345 --> 00:47:14,504
why would I still be grinding away here?

1054
00:47:17,345 --> 00:47:17,945
Your phone.

1055
00:47:22,464 --> 00:47:23,225
Hello?

1056
00:47:24,825 --> 00:47:25,384
Yes, I'm here.

1057
00:47:27,785 --> 00:47:28,664
Now?

1058
00:47:32,104 --> 00:47:33,144
Okay, coming right away.

1059
00:47:39,345 --> 00:47:40,144
What's wrong?

1060
00:47:41,144 --> 00:47:42,705
HR wants to see me.

1061
00:48:03,705 --> 00:48:04,104
Come in.

1062
00:48:20,042 --> 00:48:24,782
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

1063
00:48:29,232 --> 00:48:31,152
♪Too much of shame♪

1064
00:48:31,498 --> 00:48:34,294
♪To waste it crying♪

1065
00:48:36,752 --> 00:48:38,672
♪Leave all behind you♪

1066
00:48:38,672 --> 00:48:40,952
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

1067
00:48:41,072 --> 00:48:43,301
♪You know how far you've gone♪

1068
00:48:43,436 --> 00:48:45,712
♪In the fire you rise again♪

1069
00:48:45,898 --> 00:48:48,258
♪You made it through the worst♪

1070
00:48:48,396 --> 00:48:50,600
♪The best is yet to come♪

1071
00:48:50,843 --> 00:48:52,983
♪The best is yet to come♪

1072
00:48:55,685 --> 00:48:57,008
♪Isn't it magical♪

1073
00:48:57,008 --> 00:48:58,640
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

1074
00:48:58,672 --> 00:49:01,139
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

1075
00:49:01,139 --> 00:49:03,592
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

1076
00:49:03,673 --> 00:49:06,321
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

1077
00:49:06,410 --> 00:49:08,941
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

1078
00:49:09,021 --> 00:49:11,243
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

1079
00:49:11,385 --> 00:49:12,466
♪But I don't want to♪

1080
00:49:12,575 --> 00:49:14,841
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

1081
00:49:14,957 --> 00:49:16,022
♪Until 3 AM♪

1082
00:49:16,193 --> 00:49:17,398
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

1083
00:49:17,552 --> 00:49:18,785
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

1084
00:49:18,876 --> 00:49:21,240
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

1085
00:49:21,387 --> 00:49:25,797
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

1086
00:49:40,522 --> 00:49:41,958
♪Leave all behind you♪

1087
00:49:42,062 --> 00:49:44,549
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

1088
00:49:44,732 --> 00:49:46,861
♪You know how far you've gone♪

1089
00:49:47,048 --> 00:49:49,388
♪In the fire you rise again♪

1090
